The new proposition has been designed so customers can split purchases into several repayments. The bank hopes to fill some of the growing demand for buy now pay later schemes as well as making it “better and safer”.   NatWest customers can now use the buy now pay later scheme almost anywhere that accepts a Mastercard. The proposition will also provide controls and safeguards including credit and affordability checks. These measures are implemented to ensure the product is right for the customer before they start to spend. READ MORE: Pension death benefits may be at risk in Rishi Sunak’s spring statement - ‘too generous!’